dated statements of redeemable convertible preferred stock and [shareholders\' equity]."\n\n**Implied per-share price:** ~$50.85/share ($600M ÷ 11.8M shares)\n\n### Cash Flow Statement Corroboration\n\nThe Consolidated Statement of Cash Flows confirms aggregate repurchase activity:\n\n| Period | Payments for Repurchase of Common and Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock |\n|---|---|\n| Year ended December 31, 2025 | $(1,125) million |\n| Year ended December 31, 2024 | $(1,021) million |\n| Year ended December 31, 2023 | $(170) million |\n\nThe 2024 figure of ~$1,021 million aligns with the $920M (common) + $101M (preferred) = $1,021M disclosed in the narrative. The 2025 figure of ~$1,125 million aligns with $522M (SpaceX common) + $600M (xAI common) = $1,122M, plus minor rounding or additional transactions.\n\n---\n\n## Basis for Repurchase/Tender Pricing\n\nThe filing provides explicit language on how repurchase prices were determined:\n\n> **"The Company only repurchased shares held by eligible participants for more than six months at a purchase price per share equal to the then current fair market value."**\n\nAnd separately, regarding the preferred stock repurchases:\n\n> "...in a number of unrelated transactions with existing shareholders **at their then-current fair market value**."\n\n### Key Pricing Principles Disclosed:\n\n1. **Pricing benchmark:** "Then current fair market value" — the filing does not specify a separate valuation methodology (e.g., 409A valuation, third-party appraisal, or discounted cash flow), but references fair market value as the governing standard.\n\n2. **Holding period requirement:** Shares had to be held by eligible participants for **more than six months** before repurchase.\n\n3. **Eligible participants:** "Eligible current and former employees" and "existing shareholders" — the filing does not specify whether all existing shareholders were eligible or only certain classes.\n\n4. **Transaction structure:** Described as "a number of unrelated transactions" rather than a formal, pro-rata tender offer, suggesting bilateral negotiated repurchases at fair market value rather than a fixed-price tender.\n\n5. **Retirement of shares:** "All SpaceX shares repurchased to date have been retired" and "All xAI shares repurchased to date have been retired" — repurchased shares were not held as treasury stock.\n\n---\n\n## Stock Splits\n\nThe filing references stock splits in two contexts:\n\n### 1. Capitalization Assumptions (Preamble)\n\n> "The actual number of shares that may be issued will be determined based on a future trading price and is subject to customary adjustments for **reclassifications, recapitalization, stock splits** or any other similar event affecting the outstanding capital stock of [Cursor] or the..."\n\nThis language appears in the context of convertible securities and the assumptions underlying share count calculations, indicating that the conversion ratios and share counts are subject to adjustment for stock splits.\n\n### 2. No Specific Stock Split Disclosed\n\nThe provided chunks **do not disclose any specific stock split** that has occurred or is planned. The references are standard protective/adjustment language only. The fee table\'s proposed maximum offering prices ($5.5 trillion to $7.5 trillion for 66,666,670 shares) imply extraordinarily high per-share values (~$82,500 to $112,500 per share), which could suggest a pre-IPO stock split may be contemplated, but **no such split is affirmatively disclosed** in the provided excerpts.\n\n---\n\n## Fee Table Context\n\nThe fee table you referenced shows proposed maximum aggregate offering prices for the **same 66,666,670 shares** escalating across five scenarios:\n\n| Shares | Proposed Maximum Offering Price |\n|---|---|\n| 66,666,670 | $5,500,000,000,000 |\n| 66,666,670 | $6,000,000,000,000 |\n| 66,666,670 | $6,500,000,000,000 |\n| 66,666,670 | $7,000,000,000,000 |\n| 66,666,670 | $7,500,000,000,000 |\n\nThis implies per-share