    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output='# Share Repurchases and Fair Market Value Disclosures\n\n## Share Repurchase Activities (2024–2026)\n\nThe filing details substantial repurchase activity across SpaceX and xAI common and preferred stock:\n\n| Period | Security | Amount | Shares | Counterparties |\n|--------|----------|--------|--------|----------------|\n| Year ended Dec 31, 2025 | SpaceX Common Stock | $522 million | 14.0 million | Eligible current and former employees |\n| Year ended Dec 31, 2024 | SpaceX Common Stock | $920 million | 38.7 million | Eligible current/former employees and existing shareholders |\n| Year ended Dec 31, 2024 | SpaceX Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock | $101 million | 0.1 million | Existing shareholders |\n| Year ended Dec 31, 2025 | xAI Common Stock | $600 million | 11.8 million | Existing shareholder of xAI |\n| Three months ended Mar 31, 2026 | SpaceX Common Stock | $2,413 million | 25.4 million | Eligible current and former xAI employees (xAI Merger) |\n| Three months ended Mar 31, 2026 | SpaceX Common Stock + Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock | $1,933 million | 30.5 million + 2.1 million | Existing shareholders |\n| Three months ended Mar 31, 2025 | SpaceX Common Stock | $508 million | 28.0 million | Eligible current/former employees and existing shareholders |\n\nAll SpaceX and xAI shares repurchased to date have been retired.\n\n## Fair Market Value Determination for Repurchases\n\nThe filing\'s disclosure regarding fair market value for repurchases is notably **limited and formulaic**. The relevant language states:\n\n> *"The Company only repurchased shares held by eligible participants for more than six months at a purchase price per share equal to the then current fair market value."*\n\nFor transactions with existing shareholders, the filing states shares were repurchased:\n\n> *"in a number of unrelated transactions with existing shareholders at their then-current fair market value."*\n\n### What the filing does NOT disclose for repurchases:\n- **No explicit reference to 409A valuations** being used to determine repurchase pricing\n- **No reference to third-party appraisals** specifically for repurchase purposes\n- **No description of the methodology** used to establish "then current fair market value" for repurchases\n- **No identification of who determined** the fair market value (board, valuation specialists, etc.)\n\n## 409A Valuations and Third-Party Appraisals — Context from Stock Option Grants\n\nWhile the repurchase section lacks methodology detail, the filing does disclose the use of 409A valuations and third-party appraisals **in the context of stock option grant pricing**, which may inform the "then current fair market value" referenced for repurchases:\n\n> *"The exercise price of each stock option granted during the 2025 Fiscal Year reflects the fair market value of a share of our Class C common stock on the date of grant and was determined based on a third-party valuation obtained in accordance with Section 409A of the Code."*\n\nAdditionally, in the Significant Accounting Policies note:\n\n> *"the Company engages valuation specialists to assist in the valuation of equity instruments."*\n\nThe Summary Compensation Table footnotes also reference specific fair market values for Class C common stock (e.g., "$37 on May 10, 2025" for RSU grants to Ms. Shotwell), suggesting a contemporaneous 409A valuation framework exists, though the filing does not explicitly link this framework to repurchase pricing.\n\n## Valuation Methodologies for Equity Awards (Separate from Repurchases)\n\nThe share-based compensation note outlines distinct methodologies depending on award type:\n\n| Award Type | Valuation Methodology |\n|------------|----------------------|\n| RSUs, RSAs, ESPP | Fair value of common stock on grant/offering date |\n| Stock options (service/performance conditions) | Black-Scholes option-pricing model |\n| CEO awards (market, service, and performance conditions) | Monte Carlo simulation model |\n\nKey Black-Scholes assumptions include:\n- Expected term: simplified method (midpoint between vesting and contractual life)\n- Expected volatility: daily historical prices of comparable public companies\n- Risk-free interest rate: U.S. Government securities rates\n- Dividend yield: 0.00% (no dividends declared or anticipated)\n\nFor the CEO\'s xAI Award specifically:\n- Expected term: 10.0 years\n- Volatility: 45%–55%\n- Risk-free interest rate: 4.06%\n- Dividend yield: 0.00%\n\n## Summary\n\nThe filing discloses that all share repurchases were conducted at "then current fair market value" and restricted to shares held by eligible participants for more than six months. However, **the filing does not explicitly disclose the specific methodology, 409A valuations, or third-party appraisals used to determine fair market value for repurchase purposes**. The 409A third-party valuation methodology is disclosed only for stock option exercise price determination, and the general engagement of valuation specialists is noted for equity instrument valuation broadly. The absence of explicit linkage between these valuation frameworks and repurchase pricing represents a gap in the disclosure.',
