formation** — retroactively adjusted for **all periods presented** in the consolidated financial statements and the prospectus.\n\n2. **SpaceX Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock conversion rate** — proportionately adjusted. Each share of SpaceX Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock became convertible into **fifty shares** of SpaceX Common Stock following the 2026 Stock Split (i.e., the pre-split rate of 10:1 multiplied by 5).\n\n3. **xAI Merger exchange ratios** — The xAI Merger exchange ratio of 0.1433 SpaceX shares per share of xAI Common Stock and the $75.46 per share cash election price are explicitly noted as being **"on a pre-2026 Stock Split basis,"** meaning they were established before the split and share counts derived from them would require multiplication by 5 for comparability.\n\n4. **EchoStar Spectrum Transaction** — The approximately 52.4 million Class A shares at $212 per share (totaling ~$11.1 billion equity consideration) are explicitly noted as **"not giv[ing] effect to the 2026 Stock Split,"** indicating those figures remain on a pre-split basis.\n\n5. **Weighted average shares for EPS** — The 3,884 million weighted average shares for Q1 2026 and 2,875 million for Q1 2025 reflect retroactive adjustment for the split.\n\n---\n\n## 2022 — Ten-for-One Stock Split ("2022 Stock Split")\n\n### Exact Language\n\n**From Note 13 (Capital Stock):**\n\n> "In 2022, the Board approved a stock split (the \'2022 Stock Split\'), pursuant to which each share of the SpaceX Common Stock issued and outstanding was split into ten shares of SpaceX Common Stock."\n\n### Key Differences from the 2026 Split\n\n| Feature | 2022 Stock Split | 2026 Stock Split |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Ratio** | 10-for-1 | 5-for-1 |\n| **Classes affected** | SpaceX Common Stock (single class at the time) | Class A, Class B, and Class C Common Stock |\n| **Effective date** | 2022 (specific date not disclosed) | May 4, 2026 |\n| **Board approval** | 2022 | May 2026 |\n| **Preferred stock conversion adjustment** | Not separately disclosed | Explicitly stated — conversion rate proportionately adjusted (to 50:1) |\n\nThe 2022 split is described more briefly, without the same level of detail regarding retroactive adjustments or preferred stock conversion rate impacts, suggesting those mechanics were either simpler (single class of common stock) or not separately enumerated in the current filing\'s notes.',
