        output='# Share Repurchase Program Disclosures\n\n## Eligibility Requirements\n\nThe disclosures indicate that repurchases were limited to **"eligible current and former employees"** and **"existing shareholders."** For transactions tied to the xAI Merger, repurchases were made from **"eligible current and former xAI employees."**\n\n## Holding Period Requirements\n\nThe company imposed a **six-month holding period** requirement. The disclosure states:\n\n> "The Company only repurchased shares held by eligible participants for **more than six months** at a purchase price per share equal to the then current fair market value."\n\nThis requirement is repeated in both the 2024/2025 annual disclosure and the Q1 2025/Q1 2026 quarterly disclosure.\n\n## Pricing Methodology\n\nThe repurchase price was based on **then-current fair market value** — not a specific third-party valuation or appraisal. The disclosure states shares were repurchased:\n\n> "...at their then-current fair market value."\n\n> "...at a purchase price per share equal to the then current fair market value."\n\nNo reference is made to a specific valuation report, appraisal, or formula-based pricing; the pricing is consistently tied to fair market value at the time of transaction.\n\n## Repurchase Activity Summary\n\n### SpaceX Common Stock\n\n| Period | Amount | Shares | Implied Price/Share |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Year ended Dec 31, 2025 | $522 million | 14.0 million | ~$37.29 |\n| Year ended Dec 31, 2024 | $920 million | 38.7 million | ~$23.77 |\n| Three months ended Mar 31, 2026 (xAI Merger) | $2,413 million | 25.4 million | ~$94.99 |\n| Three months ended Mar 31, 2026 (existing shareholders) | Part of $1,933 million | 30.5 million | — |\n| Three months ended Mar 31, 2025 | $508 million | 28.0 million | ~$18.14 |\n\n### SpaceX Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock\n\n| Period | Amount | Shares | Implied Price/Share |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Year ended Dec 31, 2024 | $101 million | 0.1 million | ~$1,010 |\n| Three months ended Mar 31, 2026 | Part of $1,933 million | 2.1 million | — |\n\n### xAI Common Stock\n\n| Period | Amount | Shares | Implied Price/Share |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Year ended Dec 31, 2025 | $600 million | 11.8 million | ~$50.85 |\n\n## Treatment of Repurchased Shares\n\nAll repurchased SpaceX and xAI shares **have been retired**:\n\n> "All SpaceX shares repurchased to date have been retired."\n> "All xAI shares repurchased to date have been retired."\n\n## Deemed Dividend Adjustment\n\nThe EPS reconciliation note discloses that the excess of fair market value over consideration transferred for repurchases of SpaceX Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock was treated as a **deemed dividend**, increasing net loss attributable to common shareholders in the loss-per-share calculation.\n\n## Total Shares Outstanding\n\nAs of May 1, 2026 (after giving effect to the Class C Reclassification, Preferred Conversion, and 2026 Stock Split):\n\n- **Class A common stock:** 6,932,508,000 shares\n- **Class B common stock:** 5,602,790,410 shares\n- **Total:** ~12.535 billion shares\n\n## Implied Valuation Observations\n\nThe rising implied per-share repurchase prices across periods (from ~$18.14 in Q1 2025 to ~$94.99 in Q1 2026 for common stock) reflect significant valuation appreciation over the timeframe, consistent with the company\'s growth trajectory and the xAI Merger. However, the company does not explicitly state an aggregate implied equity valuation based on these repurchase prices.',
